President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the appointment of Nasiru Ila as the Senior Special Assistant to the President on National Assembly Matters (House of Representatives). Malam Garba Shehu, the Presidentâ€™s media aide confirmed this development in a statement on Sunday in Abuja. Ila, a product of Victory College, Alexandria, and West London College, United Kingdom, was a successful businessman with interests in haulage, ginnery, and tannery before his foray into politics. In 2011 and 2015, he was voted into the lower chamber of the National Assembly as a member representing Tarauni Federal Constituency in Kano. According to the presidential aide, the Chartered member of the Association of National Accountants of Nigeria, (ANAN), replaces Umar El-Yakub who has been appointed Minister by the president. 